title: Raith 1-2 Hibernian: Match Report
text:
Raith 1-2 Hibernian: Match Report 24 Oct 2015 17:01:00 
comments Jason Cummings on target again as Hibernian edge RaithJason Cummings scored his 10th goal of the season as Hibernian beat Raith 2-1 to make it six Scottish Championship wins out of seven.The visitors needed just three minutes to open the scoring as John McGinn smashed a left-footed shot into the top corner after being teed up by Dominique Malonga.And Raith were left with a mountain to climb after 25 minutes when Cummings took a long ball from Mark Oxley in his stride before lifting a shot over Kevin Cuthbert and into the net.Jon Daly headed home Jason Thomson's cross in the 64th minute to give Rovers hope, but they were unable to find an equaliser.
